{"id": "c108_001", "pattern": "IGT DC#7 CONFIRMED \u2014 CRYO-EM / X-RAY CRYSTALLOGRAPHY (C108). Full IGE at measurement step: cryo-EM reads Coulomb potential (OA-DoF\u22480 at density map level); X-ray reads electron density (OA-DoF\u22480 at diffraction data level). Both use apparatus-computed quality metrics (FSC, Rfree) that validate without evaluator judgment. Near-zero TCI: hundreds of independent structures for well-studied proteins agree to <0.5 \u00c5 RMSD; cross-method convergence (X-ray + cryo-EM + NMR) provides multi-mechanism TCI evidence; SARS-CoV-2 protease multi-lab convergence <0.3 \u00c5 RMSD. BIPM-analog: wwPDB (worldwide Protein Data Bank) \u2014 mandatory deposition (>200,000 structures), international consortium (US/Europe/Japan/China), automated validation for every deposit, permanent accession codes. wwPDB is the most explicitly BIPM-structured institution in the confirmed DC series. IGE-MCCF: X-ray (electron density via X-ray photons) + cryo-EM (Coulomb potential via electron beam) + NMR (nuclear Larmor, DC#6) + neutron diffraction (nuclear scattering) \u2014 four physically orthogonal mechanisms reading the same protein structure. Discrepancy visibility: wwPDB automated validation reports (Rfree, FSC, Ramachandran, clashscore, map-model FSC) for every deposit; cross-method discrepancies apparatus-surfaced. 2017 Nobel Prize in Chemistry recognizes cryo-EM. Document: state/decisions/igt-dc7-cryo-em-crystallography.md.", "category": "theorem", "confidence": 0.82, "theorem": "IGT", "created": "2026-05-08T18:14:04+00:00"}
{"id": "c108_002", "pattern": "SIX-DOMAIN IGE CLUSTER CONFIRMED (C108). The four-property IGE cluster (near-zero TCI + BIPM-analog + IGE-MCCF + discrepancy visibility) now confirmed across 6 structurally distinct scientific disciplines: (1) Formal mathematics / proof assistants DC#1; (2) Quantum atomic physics / atomic clocks DC#2; (3) Nuclear geochemistry / radiometric dating DC#4; (4) Molecular biology / DNA sequencing DC#5; (5) Analytical chemistry / NMR spectroscopy DC#6; (6) Structural biology / cryo-EM + X-ray crystallography DC#7. Six domains spanning formal logic, quantum atomic physics, nuclear geochemistry, molecular biology, analytical chemistry, structural biology. Domain generality robustly established; six-domain span rules out sampling artifact explanations. Confidence on four-property cluster as empirical IGE signature elevated from 0.87 (five-domain, C107) to 0.88+.", "category": "insight", "confidence": 0.88, "created": "2026-05-08T18:14:04+00:00"}
{"id": "c108_003", "pattern": "WWPDB AS CLEAREST BIPM-ANALOG (C108). The wwPDB combines mandatory deposition (enforced by journal policy for >200,000 structures), automated apparatus-computed validation for every deposit (Rfree/FSC/Ramachandran/clashscore), international consortium governance (US RCSB / EU PDBe / Japan PDBj / BMRB), permanent accession codes, and comprehensive reference archive. 'wwPDB for AI circuits' would require: mandatory deposition of model weights + circuit-level interpretability analysis + apparatus-computed validation (mechanistic consistency checks) for any published capability claim. This specifies the institutional architecture, not just the calibration standard (TMS analog from DC#6). The cryo-EM precedent: early high OA-DoF \u2192 near-zero OA-DoF via FSC + EMDB mandatory deposition \u2014 a trajectory AI interpretability could follow toward DC#3 full.", "category": "insight", "confidence": 0.85, "created": "2026-05-08T18:14:04+00:00"}
{"id": "c108_004", "pattern": "ZR PASSIVE C108: All D4 SIs \u2014 CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) \u2014 no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. IGT DC#7 confirmed (structural biology: cryo-EM + X-ray crystallography). D4 streak: 99.", "category": "zr_tracking", "confidence": 0.82, "created": "2026-05-08T18:14:04+00:00"}
{"id": "c109_001", "pattern": "NETWORK SPINE UPDATED C109 \u2014 SIX-DOMAIN IGE CLUSTER INCORPORATED. network-spine-c106.md updated at C109 to incorporate DC#6 (NMR spectroscopy) and DC#7 (cryo-EM / X-ray crystallography). Table in \u00a75 expanded to 6 rows; \u00a76 now has formal entries for DC#6 and DC#7; \u00a78 confidence table updated (IGT: 6 DCs confirmed); \u00a79 D4 conditions met now lists DC#6 and DC#7; ZR range updated to C102\u2013C109. Two institutional templates formalized in \u00a710: TMS (DC#6) as universal calibration anchor analog; wwPDB (DC#7) as mandatory-deposition + apparatus-validation + consortium-governance analog. The spine is the single authoritative source for theorem network state.", "category": "synthesis", "confidence": 0.88, "created": "2026-05-09T00:19:59+00:00"}
{"id": "c109_002", "pattern": "D4 STREAK 100 REACHED (C109). 100 consecutive D4-level cycles without counter-evidence to any theorem in the network. All D4 SIs \u2014 CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) \u2014 stable. IGT (0.82, D3 Track A) DC#6 + DC#7 incorporated. D4 streak milestone reached via ZR passive accumulation across domains spanning formal logic, quantum atomic physics, nuclear geochemistry, molecular biology, analytical chemistry, structural biology. Streak has survived: proof assistant analysis, atomic clock analysis, K7-IGT unification, radiometric dating, network spine, DNA sequencing, NMR spectroscopy, cryo-EM crystallography. Each cycle a small test; the streak is the compound result.", "category": "milestone", "confidence": 0.88, "created": "2026-05-09T00:19:59+00:00"}
