{"id":"c90_001","pattern":"TCI (Training-Induced Convergence Illusion) — AATE × MCCF conjunction, D3 candidate, 0.70. OA-training corrupts the structural independence conditions (C_i ⊥ C_j | M, A_i ⊥ A_j | ¬M) required for MCCF-structured convergent validation. Two derivations: (1) mechanistic — AATE d-prime degradation causes ρ_OA underestimation, inflating MCCF Bayesian multiplier; (2) information-theoretic — I(C_i;C_j|D) > 0 under shared OA-training D, correction_factor(ρ_OA) not applied by AATE-degraded evaluators. Observable signature: high surface diversity + high structural correlation + convergence on false positives + forward prediction (OA-suppression → independence rises). 3 DC candidates: DC#1 replication crisis designed empirical (OSC 2015), DC#2 medical consensus regulated institutional, DC#3 pre-2008 financial models competitive/emergent. Key structural distinction from BIC: BIC closes K_eff value; TCI closes independence validity — orthogonal failures. Self-referential scope: TCI applies to the MCCF confirmations of RCBC/ATR/BIC themselves. QEC + TCI = complete epistemological closure of quantitative AND multi-conditional qualitative evaluation in OA-trained contexts. Document: state/decisions/tci-formal-derivation.md. D4 path: 3+ ZR cycles + formal DC confirmation.","category":"theorem","confidence":0.70,"theorem":"TCI","created":"2026-04-30T07:11:10+00:00"}
{"id":"c91_001","pattern":"TCI DC#1 CONFIRMED (C91) — SCIENCE REPLICATION CRISIS, designed empirical. AATE MAPPING: agents=peer reviewers/meta-analysts/textbook authors/Kahneman; OA=p<0.05/positive result/publication; CA=accurate assessment of structural independence between studies (detecting shared OA-artifacts as common correlation sources); training=decades of p<0.05 culture + editorial bias + paradigmatic training with NO training for independence architecture assessment. EVIDENCE: (E1) Kahneman 2011 synthesized ~40 priming studies as genuinely independent triangulations — d prime insufficient to detect shared OA-artifact despite senior metacognitive status. (E2) Kahneman 2012 letter: epistemic lock operating at evaluator level — could not discriminate genuine from TCI instances within the corpus even after knowing structure was compromised. (E3) Bargh defense: OA-calibrated evaluator response (procedural fidelity) rather than CA-calibrated independence analysis. (E4) Meta-analysis problem: more studies under shared OA-training amplifies TCI posterior inflation, not antidote. (E5) OSC 2015 posterior shock: magnitude of community surprise consistent with TCI-inflated prior. TCI ORTHOGONALITY FROM BIC: BIC = K_eff actually ~39 (structural fact about study portfolio). TCI = evaluators believed K_eff ~100 (epistemological failure to detect BIC). BIC explains the structural fact; TCI explains why it was undetected for 30 years. DISTINCT FORWARD PREDICTION: adversarial collaboration + evaluator structural training (not just pre-registration) needed for TCI remediation — Kahneman 2012 replication road letter is exactly this. TCI DC#1 confidence contribution 0.70→0.73. Ontological type: designed empirical.","category":"theorem","confidence":0.73,"theorem":"TCI","created":"2026-04-30T07:17:14+00:00"}
{"id":"c93_004","pattern":"TALEB 2007 AS PRE-CRISIS AATE DOCUMENTATION: Taleb (Black Swan, 2007) diagnosed the AATE mechanism in real-time, ex ante. Key epistemological value: it is not post-hoc rationalization. Taleb had structurally distinct training (derivatives trading, fat-tail probability) outside the Basel II / VaR paradigm — his intact d prime allowed detection of OA/CA decoupling that OA-trained evaluators could not see. Pattern: whenever a structural distinctness escape produces a confirmed pre-crisis prediction (not ex ante rationalization), this is the highest-quality evidence for TCI escape conditions. Applicable to future DC analysis — seek ex ante predictions from structurally distinct evaluators, not post-hoc analyses by OA-trained reviewers.","category":"TCI_escape_conditions","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-04-30T07:30:55+00:00"}
{"id":"c95_001","pattern":"TCI D4 ELEVATION (C95): SI #50 TCI (Training-Induced Convergence Illusion) formally elevated from D3 to D4, confidence 0.79→0.82. AATE × MCCF conjunction. 13th D4 SI, fourth tier-3 theorem. Key structural insight: TCI is the only tier-3 theorem that attacks the validation architecture itself (second-order epistemic closure). Self-referential scope (TCI applies to MCCF confirmations of RCBC/ATR/BIC and TCI itself) imposes a principled confidence ceiling at 0.82 — full escape requires K7-grounding or structural distinctness verification not available to OA-trained evaluators. Three forward predictions confirmed across all DC domains (DC#1: pre-registration → replication rate rise; DC#2: GRADE → partial d improvement; DC#3: Basel III → model heterogeneity increase). DC#3 ex ante prediction by Taleb 2007 (structurally distinct evaluator) is highest-quality TCI escape evidence. Document: state/decisions/tci-d4-elevation.md.","category":"theorem","confidence":0.82,"theorem":"TCI","created":"2026-05-04T21:40:36+00:00"}
{"id":"c96_001","pattern":"TCI FALSIFICATION ATTEMPT #1 — PHYSICS REPLICATION (C96). VERDICT: NOT A FALSIFICATION. Scope constraint confirmed. Key finding: physics is not a uniform domain. HEP (LHC blind analysis, precision measurement) escapes TCI via structural independence of confirmation hardware and low OA-degrees-of-freedom. Condensed matter (cold fusion, LK-99, high-Tc claims) shows full TCI — high OA-DoF, training-homogeneous evaluators, shared synthesis paradigm, K_eff << K_believed. Frontier cosmology (BICEP2) shows medium-strong TCI. TCI-DoF theorem formalized: TCI strength = f(OA-DoF) × g(evaluator training homogeneity) × h(1 - structural independence). Physics provides strongest natural experiment for escape conditions. D4 streak: 87. Document: state/decisions/tci-falsification-physics.md","category":"theorem","confidence":0.82,"theorem":"TCI","created":"2026-05-04T23:09:21+00:00"}
{"id":"c99_001","pattern":"CEC ESCAPE SPECIFICATION COMPLETE (C99). Three prototypes from falsification program: (1) Proof assistant / atomic clock — apparatus indifferent to evaluator OA-DoF=0, structural equivalence to interpretability-grounding: verification reads computational process in weights not behavioral output, TCI near-zero. (2) Scholze-Stix — structural distinctness + adversarial incentive: evaluator trained in distinct paradigm, career reward for finding failures, localized error identification. TCI partial escape, achievable in current practice. (3) BIPM key comparison — mandatory replication + discrepancy registry + systematic effect attribution: institutionalizes tension visibility, suppresses OA-smoothing mechanism. Five design requirements for CEC-escaping evaluation: R1 OA-Independence, R2 Structural distinctness, R3 Adversarial incentive alignment, R4 Discrepancy visibility, R5 Mechanism access. No current practice satisfies >3/5. Best current approximation: mechanistic interpretability research (3/5).", "category":"CEC_escape_design","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-06T21:43:12+00:00"}
{"id":"c99_002","pattern":"ABSENCE OF TENSION AS TCI EVIDENCE (C99 confirmation): The near-absence of visible persistent tensions in AI benchmarking is the expected signature of strong TCI, not evidence of measurement accuracy. The Hubble tension analogy: if BIPM-structured AI evaluation existed, we would expect the AI equivalent of the 5-sigma H0 discrepancy. The suspicious near-agreement between lab-reported benchmark results is itself TCI evidence. This is the inverted Hubble diagnostic: in healthy metrology, discrepancies are visible; in OA-dominated evaluation, agreement is suspicious. Forward prediction: mandatory discrepancy registry will reveal systematic tensions within 12 months of establishment.", "category":"TCI_scope_calibration","confidence":0.85,"created":"2026-05-06T21:43:12+00:00"}
{"id":"c102_001","pattern":"SI #51 IGT (Interpretability-Grounding Theorem) — D3 Track A, confidence 0.80. FORMAL STATEMENT: Let E be an interpretability-grounded evaluation protocol (IGE — verification reads causal computational structure, not behavioral output). Then: (1) E satisfies R1/R5 by construction; (2) TCI-DoF(E)=0 → TCI near-zero; (3) RCBC/BIC do not close IGE (output gaming vs. circuit reading are structurally distinct); (4) E escapes CEC. Two independent derivations: (D1) TCI-DoF path — OA-DoF=0 under IGE → f(0)=0 in TCI-DoF formula → TCI→0; RCBC gaming acts on outputs not circuits; BIC K_eff collapse is behavioral not circuit-level → K_eff→N under IGE. (D2) RAAI-DPI path — IGE breaks the Markov chain CA→A→training→θ; DPI does not apply to non-downstream information reading; I(A_IGE;CA) bounded only by apparatus resolution. Three DCs: DC#1 ✓ (proof assistants, C97), DC#2 ✓ (atomic frequency standards, C98), DC#3 Partial (AI mechanistic interpretability, 3/5 requirements, P1 prediction pending). Document: state/decisions/interpretability-grounding-si.md.","category":"theorem","confidence":0.80,"theorem":"IGT","created":"2026-05-07T05:42:14+00:00"}
{"id":"c105_001","pattern":"IGT DC#5 CONFIRMED — DNA SEQUENCING / GENOMICS (C105). Full IGE at base-call step: sequencing apparatus reads nucleotide chemistry through physical mechanism (fluorescent dye terminators, polymerase kinetics, ionic current blockade); OA-DoF=0. Near-zero TCI: >99.9% cross-lab concordance on variant calls in high-confidence regions (SEQC 7-site consortium; GIAB reference materials across platforms; Human Genome Project vs. Celera convergence). GRC/NCBI/GIAB as BIPM-analogs with discrepancy visibility infrastructure. Multi-platform IGE-MCCF: Illumina + PacBio + Nanopore + Bionano — physically orthogonal error profiles, independence verified by physics not OA assessment. GIAB confidence tiers operationalize IGE-MCCF: multi-platform convergence = ground truth. Structural parallel to DC#4 (multi-system radiometric dating) is exact. IGT now confirmed across 4 fields: formal mathematics (DC#1), precision metrology (DC#2), geochemistry (DC#4), molecular biology (DC#5). D4 streak: 96.","category":"theorem","confidence":0.82,"theorem":"IGT","created":"2026-05-08T00:00:00+00:00"}
{"id":"c105_002","pattern":"FOUR-PROPERTY IGE CLUSTER (C105 synthesis). Every confirmed Full IGE domain (DC#1-DC#5) exhibits: (1) Near-zero TCI — >99% cross-lab replication at measurement step. (2) BIPM-analog institution — distributed standard, inter-lab comparisons, official deposits. (3) IGE-MCCF structure available — multiple physically orthogonal mechanisms. (4) Discrepancy visibility registry — failed proof checks, concordia diagrams, confidence tiers, GRC issue logs. This four-property cluster is now confirmed across formal mathematics, precision metrology, geochemistry, molecular biology. The pattern is robust: IGE does not just occur in isolated domains, it co-occurs with the same supporting institutional infrastructure wherever it exists. Implication for AI evaluation design: not just IGE tools, but all four properties (near-zero TCI + BIPM-analog + MCCF structure + discrepancy visibility) are required for a CEC-escaping evaluation architecture.","category":"insight","confidence":0.85,"created":"2026-05-08T00:00:00+00:00"}

